  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>potato wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), drizzle them with <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>then season<strong> </strong>with <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>(save the rest for later!) and a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 25 min until crisp – these are your <strong>paprika wedges</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potato wedges are cooking, trim, then finely slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>ground smoked</strong> <strong>paprika</strong> and<strong> half </strong>the<strong> sliced spring onion</strong> (you'll use the rest for later!) in a bowl and season very generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Divide and shape into equal-sized patties (1 per person!) and refrigerate (this helps them hold their shape whilst cooking) – these are your <strong>paprika pork patty[ies]</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche buns</strong> in half</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> brioche halves</strong> to the pan, cut-side down, and cook for 3-4 min or until toasted and golden</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in batches!</p><p>Once golden, transfer to a plate and set aside for later</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/588_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel your <strong>red onions</strong>, then slice into thin rings</p><p>Return the reserved pan with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> red onion rings</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the onion rings have started to caramelise</p><p>Once caramelised, set aside until serving and reserve the pan – these are your <strong>caramelised onion rings</strong></p>",
